Great App, for knot tying.
Love the photos and tutorials. Scrolling from one photo to the next, however, is not smooth and often catches. Great content, just needs smoothed out in operation.
Another brill way to vary your puzzle solving. Learn it, practice, see if you can repeat in 1 hour, 1 day or 1 week. Like it.
You carry knots in your mind and now on your mobile phone.
Very good instructions of useful knots.

Love it. Hope you'll add the estar hitch for use with slippery synthetics like Dyneema. Maybe some splices would be handy too, like Brummel etc. I prefer this over video - please don't feel the need to go video. Photos better for offline and easier to follow. Video is a pain as often flies by too fast to get it. Thx.
Good layout right to the point.

Loved it! I've been tying my shoelaces the same way for over sixty years. Tried the Secure Shoelace knot today. I went for a long walk to try it out. Trying not to think of how many hours I've spent retying shoelaces!

Good app, I chose this over 3-4 similar apps for its clear demarcation of jamming, non-jamming, and quick-release knots. Would like the favorites to carry over from the free app. Note to potential users: Favorites list appears only after you select your first favorite knot.
replyContent: Do not fix what's not broken.

content: I really like the pictures.  Everything is simple and clear. This has all the knots I need for scouts except 1:      Two half-hitches  I know that that one is similar to the clove hitch, but one of your demos would make it clear to kids and their parents to figure out the knot. Thanks!
Very nice app. I bought the pro version. Currently covering over 80 knots with excellent pictures and good instructions. Good search function and categories

Well illustrated, intuitive interface, precise, complete, stable. I keep a piece of cord on my keyring and often practice various knots on my daily train commute. A welcome change from Sudoku, scrabble, crosswords etc. I purchased the pro version voluntarily in support of good simple no-frills software. An easy 5.
Awsome app for reminding you how to tie them important knots,
Simple, effective, accurate. This app is a nessesary addition in your tool kit for life. Be safe, use the the right knots!
Well made, easy to comprehend. Liked it enough to support the developer by purchasing the pro version
Simple, fast, informative.

This is one of those rare "killer apps" I run across once in a blue moon. I frequently try to work out how to best secure things w/ binding, rope, etc but know painfully little about knot tying. This app is an excellent reference. Beautifully simple in its execution as well. üëç

very usefull for daily life application ..great apps
I felt I should purchase this as a thank you for showing me a better way of tying show laces!

Enough knots to be useful to a beginner like me, lots of clear photos, great instructions, and explanations of how each knot is useful. A simple, organized, clean navigation interface. All for a very reasonable price. Highly recommended.
